@startuml mouse-chords
title Input server — logical button/chord synthesis state machine (spec 04, ADR-0004)
skinparam shadowing false

[*] --> Idle

state Idle {
}
state "B1 active\n(sweep in progress)" as B1 {
}
state "B1+B2 chord\n⇒ core sees Cut gesture" as Cut {
}
state "B1+B3 chord\n⇒ core sees Paste gesture" as Paste {
}
state "B2 active\n(execute sweep)" as B2 {
}
state "B2+B1 chord\n⇒ execute with argument" as Arg {
}
state "B3 active\n(look sweep)" as B3 {
}

Idle --> B1 : phys B1 down /\ntouch: finger 1 down
Idle --> B2 : phys B2 down / Alt+B1 down /\ntouch: two-finger tap / chordbar 2
Idle --> B3 : phys B3 down / Meta+B1 down /\ntouch: three-finger tap or long-press
B1 --> Idle : B1 up (click or sweep done)
B2 --> Idle : B2 up
B3 --> Idle : B3 up

B1 --> Cut : phys B2 down /\nAlt pressed mid-sweep /\ntouch: 2nd finger tap /\nchordbar 2 tapped
B1 --> Paste : phys B3 down /\nMeta pressed mid-sweep /\ntouch: 2nd finger double-tap
Cut --> B1 : chord button/modifier up\n(buttons=1 again)
Paste --> B1 : chord button/modifier up
Cut --> Paste : B3/Meta while chorded\n(snarf+paste idiom)

B2 --> Arg : phys B1 down /\nmodifier released, B1 still down? see note
Arg --> B2 : B1 up

note right of Cut
  Emitted on /dev/mouse as ordinary
  Plan 9 events: buttons 1 → 3 → 1.
  The core runs unmodified ACME logic;
  it cannot tell emulation from hardware.
end note

note bottom of Arg
  2-1 chord (execute with argument).
  In the modifier profile: hold Alt, press
  pointer button (=B2 sweep), release Alt
  while holding (=B1 join).
end note
@enduml
